-- Boryszew May Replace PBG in Warsaw’s WIG20 Index, Trigon Says
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-01-18T14:57:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/boryszew-may-replace-pbg-in-warsaw-s-wig20-index-trigon-says.html
Boryszew SA (BRS) , the chemical and
automotive company controlled by Polish billionaire Roman
Karkosik, may replace  PBG SA (PBG)  in Warsaw’s benchmark  WIG20 Index (WIG20) 
in March, Trigon brokerage said in an e-mailed research note.  The criteria for joining the index include free float and
trading volume, according to the rules of the Warsaw Stock
Exchange. The ranking will be prepared on Jan. 31 and the
revision will take place after the close of the session on March
16.  The industrial group Boryszew makes products ranging from
antifreeze to forklifts while PBG is the Poland’s third-largest
building company.  PBG shares, the best-performing stock in WIG2O Index this
year, fell 1.1 percent to 83 zloty at 3:12 p.m. in Warsaw
trading while Boryszew stocks were unchanged at 0.73 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw at 
